wikipedia_page.main: John Leofric Stocks DSO (26 October 1882 – 13 June 1937) was a British philosopher and was briefly Vice Chancellor of the University of Liverpool in 1937.

response: The following question appeared on 2010 CSAT, and had a correct-response rate of 9.77 percent. The paragraph is excerpted from John Leofric Stocks' "The Limits of Purpose":
She married the philosopher John Leofric Stocks in December 1913.  He was a fellow of St John's College, Oxford.  They had one son and two daughters.
